titleproper.value:
Guide to the Records of the Office of the Treasurer (Muriel L. Mantel)
                    <num>RG 10</num>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by New York University Archives staff.

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2012-09-27T14:49-0400</date>

unittitle.value: Records of the Office of the Treasurer (Muriel L. Mantel)

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: This collection contains administrative records of Muriel L. Mantel, Administrative Assistant to NYU's Vice President of Business Affairs and Treasurer and later NYU's Associate Treasurer. The collection is mainly related to financial records and property records.

p.value: Materials related to personnel, faculty grievances, job searches and all files with information that falls under the University's Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) policy are permanently restricted.

Published citations should take the following form:
                <lb/>
                <lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Records of the Office of the Treasurer (Muriel L. Mantel); RG 10.9; box number; folder number;
                <lb/>
                <address>
                    <addressline>New York University Archives</addressline>
                </address>

<list>
                    <item>Mantel, Muriel L, Biographical File, New York University Archives</item>
                </list>

The majority of the records are financial and include: papers having to do with real estate transactions and insurance, property taxes, building plans and blueprints, wills, trusts and endowments, planning committees, bills, budget information, press publications, patents, and correspondence. Particularly useful or relevant for researchers is material relating to NYU's property acquisitions and development, especially having to do with the building of the Medical Center, including information about buying buildings, mergers, mortgage papers, building blueprints, maintenance reports, building contracts and reports, lease agreements, tenant eviction notices, demolitions and renovations, building inspections, and community negotiations.
